entrusted (0.3.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Address more scenarios that could result into intermittent conversion failures
  * Introduce fine-grained seccomp security profile for container sandbox
  * Add setting for controlling PDF result visual quality
  * Allow multiple language selection when creating searchable PDF results
  * Provide the ability to cancel conversions that are not yet started
  * Change logo artwork along with minor visual improvements
  * Address few potential intermittent failures in batch conversions
  * Upgrade software dependencies for quality and security reasons
  * Explicitly restrict file upload size to 500 MB in the Web server

 -- Yves Zoundi <yves_zoundi@hotmail.com>  Sat, 17 Dec 2022 09:38:25 -0400

entrusted (0.2.6) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix Docker permission denied errors at the end of conversions, under Linux
  * Fix intermittent failures in batch conversions due to container process crashes
  * Make PDF result quality and size more predictable
  * Display overall progress information and final status summary
  * Add "clickable" hyperlinks in few dialogs
  * Improve look and feel consistency

 -- Yves Zoundi <yves_zoundi@hotmail.com>  Wed, 16 Nov 2022 09:38:25 -0400

entrusted (0.2.5) stable; urgency=medium

  * arm64 support for Linux and Mac OS binaries, as well as the container image
  * Small bug fixes for temporary folders handling and other minor improvements
  * New button in the Desktop client to manually check for updates

 -- Yves Zoundi <yves_zoundi@hotmail.com>  Sun, 11 Sept 2022 09:38:25 -0400

entrusted (0.2.4) stable; urgency=medium

  * Hide Microsoft Windows command prompts displayed upon conversion
  * Mitigate false positives while changing file modification dates on Windows
  * Remove UNIX/Linux specific code in the online service
  * Improve user interface "responsiveness" with better decoupling of background tasks

